article.headline: VA Commonwealth 70, Albany 67
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Eric Maynor hit a pair of free throws with 7.5 seconds remaining and D.A. Walker blocked Jamar Wilson's 3-pointer with two seconds to go Friday night, preserving Virginia Commonwealth's 70-67 victory against Albany. The Rams (17-8) went ahead to stay on Maynor's layup with 1:11 to play, producing the ninth lead change of the half. There were also nine ties. Wilson had 21 second-half points for Albany (16-9). He finished with 28. After Maynor's layup gave VCU a 66-64 lead, Wilson made 1 of 2 free throws with 46 seconds left. Jamal Shuler's 12-footer boosted the Rams' lead to three, but Lucious Jordan's putback with 9 seconds left pulled the Great Danes back to within a point. Maynor's free throws capped a solid half for the Rams, who were 15-for-24 from the field with just three turnovers, and allowed them to overcome a 32-19 rebounding disadvantage. The Great Danes had a 19-5 edge on the boards after halftime. Nick George led the Rams with 23 points and Alexander Harper had 11. Brent Wilson added 17 points for Albany. The game was one of 50 so-called ESPN BracketBusters, giving teams expected to battle for at-large NCAA tournament berths a chance to add a solid victory late in the season.
